li>WooCommerce 2.2.2 compatibility is added.</li>\n<li>Minor style fixes.</li>\n<li>Dynamic alt tag in the top logo is added.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.2.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>CSS improvements for mobile devices.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.9</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>ADDED: Compatibility with WooCommerce 2.1.7</li>\n<li>FIXED: Logo width is now same on the product pages as on the homepage.</li>\n<li>FIXED: Yellow background color on product count number under each category is removed on the main category page.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.8</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>ADDED: Compatibility with WooCommerce 2.1.5</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.7</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Minor WooCommerce template update.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.6</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Theme is now compatible with WooCommerce 2.1+ .</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Top menu bug is fixed, it will not be displayed if menu location is not defined.</li>\n<li>Navigation label is now displayed on top of the menu for mobile devices.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improving product pagination on category pages.</li>\n<li>Update theme functionality is now improved.</li>\n<li>Enabling Product Gallery images on the product page.</li>\n<li>Description and Product tabs on a product page are now responsive.</li>\n<li>Adding light_rounded Pretty Photo theme.</li>\n<li>Twitter widget is removed. Reason for this is that Twitter has discontinued its unauthenticated v1.0 API! Twitter wants your only option for on-page widgets to be their own Embedded Timelines that you can use in the default Text widget.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improving language translation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixing product variation problem.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Implementing WooShop notifier</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 2.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updating CSS to work with the Woocommerce 2.0.12</li>\n<li>Fixing Email Order Items bug .</li>\n<li>Adding Login/Logout to the top menu .</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.2.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updating number of items in cart in the upper right corner so that it works in the Woocommerce 2.0 .</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adding dynamic link to the View Cart page on the upper right shopping cart icon.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update engine changes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial theme version.</li>\n</ul>\n]]>\n	</changelog>\n</notifier>','yes'),(1237,'notifier-cache-last-updated-wooshoplite-2-2-3','1420192602','yes'),(1238,'optionsframework','a:2:{s:2:\"id\";s:11:\"wooshoplite\";s:12:\"knownoptions\";a:1:{i:0;s:11:\"wooshoplite\";}}','yes'),(1239,'_site_transient_update_themes','O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:12:\"last_checked\";i:1420192615;s:7:\"checked\";a:4:{s:7:\"mystile\";s:5:\"1.3.4\";s:14:\"twentyfourteen\";s:3:\"1.2\";s:9:\"vardhaman\";s:3:\"0.1\";s:11:\"wooshoplite\";s:5:\"2.2.3\";}s:8:\"response\";a:1:{s:14:\"twentyfourteen\";a:4:{s:5:\"theme\";s:14:\"twentyfourteen\";s:11:\"new_version\";s:3:\"1.3\";s:3:\"url\";s:43:\"https://wordpress.org/themes/twentyfourteen\";s:7:\"package\";s:60:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/theme/twentyfourteen.1.3.zip\";}}s:12:\"translations\";a:0:{}}','yes'),(1240,'wooshoplite','a:25:{s:23:\"dessky_sidebar_position\";s:4:\"left\";s:16:\"dessky_logo_type\";s:9:\"imagelogo\";s:16:\"dessky_site_name\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"dessky_tagline\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"dessky_logo_image\";s:78:\"http://192.168.1.33/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Shop_Logo1-300x51.png\";s:14:\"dessky_favicon\";s:68:\"http://192.168.1.33/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/favicon.ico\";s:13:\"dessky_footer\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"dessky_google\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"dessky_body_background\";a:5:{s:5:\"color\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"image\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"repeat\";s:6:\"repeat\";s:8:\"position\";s:10:\"top center\";s:10:\"attachment\";s:6:\"scroll\";}s:19:\"dessky_twitter_link\";s:36:\"http://www.twitter.com/your-username\";s:20:\"dessky_facebook_link\";s:37:\"http://www.facebook.co